Max Verschuuren, 21, was bent over emptying rocks out of his boot on Saturday night when a friend mistook him for a deer .
He tumbled down the hill and fell into the bushes in the Te Urewera forest, North Island .
His mate, who shot him at the back of his shoulder, was mortified to see the gaping wound on his back .
Police are investigating the incident and are warning hunters to take appropriate safety measures .